Those parts are components/tc358743/ and components/video_pipeline/capture_hw.c,
modified from the originals. They carry the TC358743 bring-up sequence and the
direct MIPI_CSI_BRIDGE register programming - the reverse engineering that made
this hardware usable in the first place. Everything else in this repository was
written for this project.

The TC358743 register order also follows the Linux kernel driver
drivers/media/i2c/tc358743.c and the Toshiba TC358743XBG functional
specification.

The interface icons in web/src/components/Icon.vue were drawn for this project
following the conventions of the Feather and Lucide icon sets - a 24x24 box,
2px strokes, round caps and joins. Drawn to those conventions, several shapes
came out close to theirs, and the gear is close enough that calling it original
would be a stretch. Both sets are permissively licensed and are acknowledged
